31/*
32 * interpret a 32 bit dos packed date/time to some parameters
33 */
34static void
35interpret_dos_date(uint32_t date, struct tm *tp)
36{
37 uint32_t p0, p1, p2, p3;
38
39 p0 = date & 0xFF;
40 p1 = ((date & 0xFF00) >> 8) & 0xFF;
41 p2 = ((date & 0xFF0000) >> 16) & 0xFF;
42 p3 = ((date & 0xFF000000) >> 24) & 0xFF;
43
44 tp->tm_sec = 2 * (p0 & 0x1F);
45 tp->tm_min = ((p0 >> 5) & 0xFF) + ((p1 & 0x7) << 3);
46 tp->tm_hour = (p1 >> 3) & 0xFF;
47 tp->tm_mday = (p2 & 0x1F);
48 tp->tm_mon = ((p2 >> 5) & 0xFF) + ((p3 & 0x1) << 3) - 1;
49 tp->tm_year = ((p3 >> 1) & 0xFF) + 80;
50}

52/*
53 * common portion:
54 * create a unix date from a dos date
55 */
56static time_t
57int_unix_date(uint32_t dos_date)
58{
59 struct tm t;
60
61 if (dos_date == 0)
62 return(0);
63
64 interpret_dos_date(dos_date, &t);
65 t.tm_wday = 1;
66 t.tm_yday = 1;
67 t.tm_isdst = 0;
68
69 return (mktime(&t));
70}

72/*
73 * create a unix date from a dos date
74 * in network byte order
75 */
76static time_t
77make_unix_date(const u_char *date_ptr)
78{
79 uint32_t dos_date = 0;
80
81 dos_date = EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(date_ptr);
82
83 return int_unix_date(dos_date);
84}
85
86/*
87 * create a unix date from a dos date
88 * in halfword-swapped network byte order!
89 */
90static time_t
91make_unix_date2(const u_char *date_ptr)
92{
93 uint32_t x, x2;
94
95 x = EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(date_ptr);
96 x2 = ((x & 0xFFFF) << 16) | ((x & 0xFFFF0000) >> 16);
97 return int_unix_date(x2);
98}

100/*
101 * interpret an 8 byte "filetime" structure to a time_t
102 * It's originally in "100ns units since jan 1st 1601"
103 */
104static time_t
105interpret_long_date(const u_char *p)
106{
107 double d;
108 time_t ret;
109
110 /* this gives us seconds since jan 1st 1601 (approx) */
111 d = (EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(p + 4) * 256.0 + p[3]) * (1.0e-7 * (1 << 24));
112
113 /* now adjust by 369 years to make the secs since 1970 */
114 d -= 369.0 * 365.25 * 24 * 60 * 60;
115
116 /* and a fudge factor as we got it wrong by a few days */
117 d += (3 * 24 * 60 * 60 + 6 * 60 * 60 + 2);
118
119 if (d < 0)
120 return(0);
121
122 ret = (time_t)d;
123
124 return(ret);
125}

127/*
128 * interpret the weird netbios "name". Return the name type, or -1 if
129 * we run past the end of the buffer
130 */
131static int
132name_interpret(netdissect_options *ndo,
133 const u_char *in, const u_char *maxbuf, char *out)
134{
135 int ret;
136 int len;
137
138 if (in >= maxbuf)
139 return(-1); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
140 ND_TCHECK2(*in, 1);
141 len = (*in++) / 2;
142
143 *out=0;
144
145 if (len > 30 || len < 1)
146 return(0);
147
148 while (len--) {
149 ND_TCHECK2(*in, 2);
150 if (in + 1 >= maxbuf)
151 return(-1); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
152 if (in[0] < 'A' || in[0] > 'P' || in[1] < 'A' || in[1] > 'P') {
153 *out = 0;
154 return(0);
155 }
156 *out = ((in[0] - 'A') << 4) + (in[1] - 'A');
157 in += 2;
158 out++;
159 }
160 *out = 0;
161 ret = out[-1];
162
163 return(ret);
164
165trunc:
166 return(-1);
167}

169/*
170 * find a pointer to a netbios name
171 */
172static const u_char *
173name_ptr(netdissect_options *ndo,
174 const u_char *buf, int ofs, const u_char *maxbuf)
175{
176 const u_char *p;
177 u_char c;
178
179 p = buf + ofs;
180 if (p >= maxbuf)
181 return(NULL); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
182 ND_TCHECK2(*p, 1);
183
184 c = *p;
185
186 /* XXX - this should use the same code that the DNS dissector does */
187 if ((c & 0xC0) == 0xC0) {
188 uint16_t l;
189
190 ND_TCHECK2(*p, 2);
191 if ((p + 1) >= maxbuf)
192 return(NULL); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
193 l = EXTRACT_16BITS(p) & 0x3FFF;
194 if (l == 0) {
195 /* We have a pointer that points to itself. */
196 return(NULL);
197 }
198 p = buf + l;
199 if (p >= maxbuf)
200 return(NULL); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
201 ND_TCHECK2(*p, 1);
202 }
203 return(p);
204
205trunc:
206 return(NULL); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
207}

209/*
210 * extract a netbios name from a buf
211 */
212static int
213name_extract(netdissect_options *ndo,
214 const u_char *buf, int ofs, const u_char *maxbuf, char *name)
215{
216 const u_char *p = name_ptr(ndo, buf, ofs, maxbuf);
217 if (p == NULL)
218 return(-1); /* error (probably name going past end of buffer) */
219 name[0] = '\0';
220 return(name_interpret(ndo, p, maxbuf, name));
221}

224/*
225 * return the total storage length of a mangled name
226 */
227static int
228name_len(netdissect_options *ndo,
229 const unsigned char *s, const unsigned char *maxbuf)
230{
231 const unsigned char *s0 = s;
232 unsigned char c;
233
234 if (s >= maxbuf)
235 return(-1); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
236 ND_TCHECK2(*s, 1);
237 c = *s;
238 if ((c & 0xC0) == 0xC0)
239 return(2);
240 while (*s) {
241 if (s >= maxbuf)
242 return(-1); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
243 ND_TCHECK2(*s, 1);
244 s += (*s) + 1;
245 ND_TCHECK2(*s, 1);
246 }
247 return(PTR_DIFF(s, s0) + 1);
248
249trunc:
250 return(-1); /* name goes past the end of the buffer */
251}

253static void
254print_asc(netdissect_options *ndo,
255 const unsigned char *buf, int len)
256{
257 int i;
258 for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
259 safeputchar(ndo, buf[i]);
260}
261
262static const char *
263name_type_str(int name_type)
264{
265 const char *f = NULL;
266
267 switch (name_type) {
268 case 0: f = "Workstation"; break;
269 case 0x03: f = "Client?"; break;
270 case 0x20: f = "Server"; break;
271 case 0x1d: f = "Master Browser"; break;
272 case 0x1b: f = "Domain Controller"; break;
273 case 0x1e: f = "Browser Server"; break;
274 default: f = "Unknown"; break;
275 }
276 return(f);
277}

279void
280smb_print_data(netdissect_options *ndo, const unsigned char *buf, int len)
281{
282 int i = 0;
283
284 if (len <= 0)
285 return;
286 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[%03X] ", i));
287 for (i = 0; i < len; /*nothing*/) {
288 ND_TCHECK(buf[i]);
289 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%02X ", buf[i] & 0xff));
290 i++;
291 if (i%8 == 0)
292 ND_PRINT((ndo, " "));
293 if (i % 16 == 0) {
294 print_asc(ndo, &buf[i - 16], 8);
295 ND_PRINT((ndo, " "));
296 print_asc(ndo, &buf[i - 8], 8);
297 ND_PRINT((ndo, "\n"));
298 if (i < len)
299 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[%03X] ", i));
300 }
301 }
302 if (i % 16) {
303 int n;
304
305 n = 16 - (i % 16);
306 ND_PRINT((ndo, " "));
307 if (n>8)
308 ND_PRINT((ndo, " "));
309 while (n--)
310 ND_PRINT((ndo, " "));
311
312 n = min(8, i % 16);
313 print_asc(ndo, &buf[i - (i % 16)], n);
314 ND_PRINT((ndo, " "));
315 n = (i % 16) - n;
316 if (n > 0)
317 print_asc(ndo, &buf[i - n], n);
318 ND_PRINT((ndo, "\n"));
319 }
320 return;
321
322trunc:
323 ND_PRINT((ndo, "\n"));
324 ND_PRINT((ndo, "WARNING: Short packet. Try increasing the snap length\n"));
325}

328static void
329write_bits(netdissect_options *ndo,
330 unsigned int val, const char *fmt)
331{
332 const char *p = fmt;
333 int i = 0;
334
335 while ((p = strchr(fmt, '|'))) {
336 size_t l = PTR_DIFF(p, fmt);
337 if (l && (val & (1 << i)))
338 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%.*s ", (int)l, fmt));
339 fmt = p + 1;
340 i++;
341 }
342}

344/* convert a UCS-2 string into an ASCII string */
345#define MAX_UNISTR_SIZE 1000
346static const char *
347unistr(netdissect_options *ndo,
348 const u_char *s, uint32_t *len, int use_unicode)
349{
350 static char buf[MAX_UNISTR_SIZE+1];
351 size_t l = 0;
352 uint32_t strsize;
353 const u_char *sp;
354
355 if (use_unicode) {
356 /*
357 * Skip padding that puts the string on an even boundary.
358 */
359 if (((s - startbuf) % 2) != 0) {
360 ND_TCHECK(s[0]);
361 s++;
362 }
363 }
364 if (*len == 0) {
365 /*
366 * Null-terminated string.
367 */
368 strsize = 0;
369 sp = s;
370 if (!use_unicode) {
371 for (;;) {
372 ND_TCHECK(sp[0]);
373 *len += 1;
374 if (sp[0] == 0)
375 break;
376 sp++;
377 }
378 strsize = *len - 1;
379 } else {
380 for (;;) {
381 ND_TCHECK2(sp[0], 2);
382 *len += 2;
383 if (sp[0] == 0 && sp[1] == 0)
384 break;
385 sp += 2;
386 }
387 strsize = *len - 2;
388 }
389 } else {
390 /*
391 * Counted string.
392 */
393 strsize = *len;
394 }
395 if (!use_unicode) {
396 while (strsize != 0) {
397 ND_TCHECK(s[0]);
398 if (l >= MAX_UNISTR_SIZE)
399 break;
400 if (ND_ISPRINT(s[0]))
401 buf[l] = s[0];
402 else {
403 if (s[0] == 0)
404 break;
405 buf[l] = '.';
406 }
407 l++;
408 s++;
409 strsize--;
410 }
411 } else {
412 while (strsize != 0) {
413 ND_TCHECK2(s[0], 2);
414 if (l >= MAX_UNISTR_SIZE)
415 break;
416 if (s[1] == 0 && ND_ISPRINT(s[0])) {
417 /* It's a printable ASCII character */
418 buf[l] = s[0];
419 } else {
420 /* It's a non-ASCII character or a non-printable ASCII character */
421 if (s[0] == 0 && s[1] == 0)
422 break;
423 buf[l] = '.';
424 }
425 l++;
426 s += 2;
427 if (strsize == 1)
428 break;
429 strsize -= 2;
430 }
431 }
432 buf[l] = 0;
433 return buf;
434
435trunc:
436 return NULL;
437}

439static const u_char *
440smb_fdata1(netdissect_options *ndo,
441 const u_char *buf, const char *fmt, const u_char *maxbuf,
442 int unicodestr)
443{
444 int reverse = 0;
445 const char *attrib_fmt = "READONLY|HIDDEN|SYSTEM|VOLUME|DIR|ARCHIVE|";
446
447 while (*fmt && buf<maxbuf) {
448 switch (*fmt) {
449 case 'a':
450 ND_TCHECK(buf[0]);
451 write_bits(ndo, buf[0], attrib_fmt);
452 buf++;
453 fmt++;
454 break;
455
456 case 'A':
457 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 2);
458 write_bits(ndo, EXTRACT_LE_16BITS(buf), attrib_fmt);
459 buf += 2;
460 fmt++;
461 break;
462
463 case '{':
464 {
465 char bitfmt[128];
466 char *p;
467 int l;
468
469 p = strchr(++fmt, '}');
470 l = PTR_DIFF(p, fmt);
471
472 if ((unsigned int)l > sizeof(bitfmt) - 1)
473 l = sizeof(bitfmt)-1;
474
475 strncpy(bitfmt, fmt, l);
476 bitfmt[l] = '\0';
477 fmt = p + 1;
478 ND_TCHECK(buf[0]);
479 write_bits(ndo, buf[0], bitfmt);
480 buf++;
481 break;
482 }
483
484 case 'P':
485 {
486 int l = atoi(fmt + 1);
487 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], l);
488 buf += l;
489 fmt++;
490 while (isdigit((unsigned char)*fmt))
491 fmt++;
492 break;
493 }
494 case 'r':
495 reverse = !reverse;
496 fmt++;
497 break;
498 case 'b':
499 {
500 unsigned int x;
501 ND_TCHECK(buf[0]);
502 x = buf[0];
503 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%u (0x%x)", x, x));
504 buf += 1;
505 fmt++;
506 break;
507 }
508 case 'd':
509 {
510 unsigned int x;
511 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 2);
512 x = reverse ? EXTRACT_16BITS(buf) :
513 EXTRACT_LE_16BITS(buf);
514 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%d (0x%x)", x, x));
515 buf += 2;
516 fmt++;
517 break;
518 }
519 case 'D':
520 {
521 unsigned int x;
522 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 4);
523 x = reverse ? EXTRACT_32BITS(buf) :
524 EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(buf);
525 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%d (0x%x)", x, x));
526 buf += 4;
527 fmt++;
528 break;
529 }
530 case 'L':
531 {
532 uint64_t x;
533 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 8);
534 x = reverse ? EXTRACT_64BITS(buf) :
535 EXTRACT_LE_64BITS(buf);
536 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%" PRIu64 " (0x%" PRIx64 ")", x, x));
537 buf += 8;
538 fmt++;
539 break;
540 }
541 case 'M':
542 {
543 /* Weird mixed-endian length values in 64-bit locks */
544 uint32_t x1, x2;
545 uint64_t x;
546 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 8);
547 x1 = reverse ? EXTRACT_32BITS(buf) :
548 EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(buf);
549 x2 = reverse ? EXTRACT_32BITS(buf + 4) :
550 EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(buf + 4);
551 x = (((uint64_t)x1) << 32) | x2;
552 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%" PRIu64 " (0x%" PRIx64 ")", x, x));
553 buf += 8;
554 fmt++;
555 break;
556 }
557 case 'B':
558 {
559 unsigned int x;
560 ND_TCHECK(buf[0]);
561 x = buf[0];
562 ND_PRINT((ndo, "0x%X", x));
563 buf += 1;
564 fmt++;
565 break;
566 }
567 case 'w':
568 {
569 unsigned int x;
570 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 2);
571 x = reverse ? EXTRACT_16BITS(buf) :
572 EXTRACT_LE_16BITS(buf);
573 ND_PRINT((ndo, "0x%X", x));
574 buf += 2;
575 fmt++;
576 break;
577 }
578 case 'W':
579 {
580 unsigned int x;
581 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 4);
582 x = reverse ? EXTRACT_32BITS(buf) :
583 EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(buf);
584 ND_PRINT((ndo, "0x%X", x));
585 buf += 4;
586 fmt++;
587 break;
588 }
589 case 'l':
590 {
591 fmt++;
592 switch (*fmt) {
593
594 case 'b':
595 ND_TCHECK(buf[0]);
596 stringlen = buf[0];
597 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%u", stringlen));
598 buf += 1;
599 break;
600
601 case 'd':
602 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 2);
603 stringlen = reverse ? EXTRACT_16BITS(buf) :
604 EXTRACT_LE_16BITS(buf);
605 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%u", stringlen));
606 buf += 2;
607 break;
608
609 case 'D':
610 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 4);
611 stringlen = reverse ? EXTRACT_32BITS(buf) :
612 EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(buf);
613 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%u", stringlen));
614 buf += 4;
615 break;
616 }
617 fmt++;
618 break;
619 }
620 case 'S':
621 case 'R': /* like 'S', but always ASCII */
622 {
623 /*XXX unistr() */
624 const char *s;
625 uint32_t len;
626
627 len = 0;
628 s = unistr(ndo, buf, &len, (*fmt == 'R') ? 0 : unicodestr);
629 if (s == NULL)
630 goto trunc;
631 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s", s));
632 buf += len;
633 fmt++;
634 break;
635 }
636 case 'Z':
637 case 'Y': /* like 'Z', but always ASCII */
638 {
639 const char *s;
640 uint32_t len;
641
642 ND_TCHECK(*buf);
643 if (*buf != 4 && *buf != 2) {
644 ND_PRINT((ndo, "Error! ASCIIZ buffer of type %u", *buf));
645 return maxbuf; /* give up */
646 }
647 len = 0;
648 s = unistr(ndo, buf + 1, &len, (*fmt == 'Y') ? 0 : unicodestr);
649 if (s == NULL)
650 goto trunc;
651 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s", s));
652 buf += len + 1;
653 fmt++;
654 break;
655 }
656 case 's':
657 {
658 int l = atoi(fmt + 1);
659 ND_TCHECK2(*buf, l);
660 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%-*.*s", l, l, buf));
661 buf += l;
662 fmt++;
663 while (isdigit((unsigned char)*fmt))
664 fmt++;
665 break;
666 }
667 case 'c':
668 {
669 ND_TCHECK2(*buf, stringlen);
670 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%-*.*s", (int)stringlen, (int)stringlen, buf));
671 buf += stringlen;
672 fmt++;
673 while (isdigit((unsigned char)*fmt))
674 fmt++;
675 break;
676 }
677 case 'C':
678 {
679 const char *s;
680 s = unistr(ndo, buf, &stringlen, unicodestr);
681 if (s == NULL)
682 goto trunc;
683 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s", s));
684 buf += stringlen;
685 fmt++;
686 break;
687 }
688 case 'h':
689 {
690 int l = atoi(fmt + 1);
691 ND_TCHECK2(*buf, l);
692 while (l--)
693 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%02x", *buf++));
694 fmt++;
695 while (isdigit((unsigned char)*fmt))
696 fmt++;
697 break;
698 }
699 case 'n':
700 {
701 int t = atoi(fmt+1);
702 char nbuf[255];
703 int name_type;
704 int len;
705
706 switch (t) {
707 case 1:
708 name_type = name_extract(ndo, startbuf, PTR_DIFF(buf, startbuf),
709 maxbuf, nbuf);
710 if (name_type < 0)
711 goto trunc;
712 len = name_len(ndo, buf, maxbuf);
713 if (len < 0)
714 goto trunc;
715 buf += len;
716 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%-15.15s NameType=0x%02X (%s)", nbuf, name_type,
717 name_type_str(name_type)));
718 break;
719 case 2:
720 ND_TCHECK(buf[15]);
721 name_type = buf[15];
722 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%-15.15s NameType=0x%02X (%s)", buf, name_type,
723 name_type_str(name_type)));
724 buf += 16;
725 break;
726 }
727 fmt++;
728 while (isdigit((unsigned char)*fmt))
729 fmt++;
730 break;
731 }
732 case 'T':
733 {
734 time_t t;
735 struct tm *lt;
736 const char *tstring;
737 uint32_t x;
738
739 switch (atoi(fmt + 1)) {
740 case 1:
741 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 4);
742 x = EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(buf);
743 if (x == 0 || x == 0xFFFFFFFF)
744 t = 0;
745 else
746 t = make_unix_date(buf);
747 buf += 4;
748 break;
749 case 2:
750 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 4);
751 x = EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(buf);
752 if (x == 0 || x == 0xFFFFFFFF)
753 t = 0;
754 else
755 t = make_unix_date2(buf);
756 buf += 4;
757 break;
758 case 3:
759 ND_TCHECK2(buf[0], 8);
760 t = interpret_long_date(buf);
761 buf += 8;
762 break;
763 default:
764 t = 0;
765 break;
766 }
767 if (t != 0) {
768 lt = localtime(&t);
769 if (lt != NULL)
770 tstring = asctime(lt);
771 else
772 tstring = "(Can't convert time)\n";
773 } else
774 tstring = "NULL\n";
775 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s", tstring));
776 fmt++;
777 while (isdigit((unsigned char)*fmt))
778 fmt++;
779 break;
780 }
781 default:
782 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%c", *fmt));
783 fmt++;
784 break;
785 }
786 }
787
788 if (buf >= maxbuf && *fmt)
789 ND_PRINT((ndo, "END OF BUFFER\n"));
790
791 return(buf);
792
793trunc:
794 ND_PRINT((ndo, "\n"));
795 ND_PRINT((ndo, "WARNING: Short packet. Try increasing the snap length\n"));
796 return(NULL);
797}

799const u_char *
800smb_fdata(netdissect_options *ndo,
801 const u_char *buf, const char *fmt, const u_char *maxbuf,
802 int unicodestr)
803{
804 static int depth = 0;
805 char s[128];
806 char *p;
807
808 while (*fmt) {
809 switch (*fmt) {
810 case '*':
811 fmt++;
812 while (buf < maxbuf) {
813 const u_char *buf2;
814 depth++;
815 buf2 = smb_fdata(ndo, buf, fmt, maxbuf, unicodestr);
816 depth--;
817 if (buf2 == NULL)
818 return(NULL);
819 if (buf2 == buf)
820 return(buf);
821 buf = buf2;
822 }
823 return(buf);
824
825 case '|':
826 fmt++;
827 if (buf >= maxbuf)
828 return(buf);
829 break;
830
831 case '%':
832 fmt++;
833 buf = maxbuf;
834 break;
835
836 case '#':
837 fmt++;
838 return(buf);
839 break;
840
841 case '[':
842 fmt++;
843 if (buf >= maxbuf)
844 return(buf);
845 memset(s, 0, sizeof(s));
846 p = strchr(fmt, ']');
847 if ((size_t)(p - fmt + 1) > sizeof(s)) {
848 /* overrun */
849 return(buf);
850 }
851 strncpy(s, fmt, p - fmt);
852 s[p - fmt] = '\0';
853 fmt = p + 1;
854 buf = smb_fdata1(ndo, buf, s, maxbuf, unicodestr);
855 if (buf == NULL)
856 return(NULL);
857 break;
858
859 default:
860 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%c", *fmt));
861 fmt++;
862 break;
863 }
864 }
865 if (!depth && buf < maxbuf) {
866 size_t len = PTR_DIFF(maxbuf, buf);
867 ND_PRINT((ndo, "Data: (%lu bytes)\n", (unsigned long)len));
868 smb_print_data(ndo, buf, len);
869 return(buf + len);
870 }
871 return(buf);
872}

988/*
989 * return a SMB error string from a SMB buffer
990 */
991char *
992smb_errstr(int class, int num)
993{
994 static char ret[128];
995 int i, j;
996
997 ret[0] = 0;
998
999 for (i = 0; err_classes[i].class; i++)
1000 if (err_classes[i].code == class) {
1001 if (err_classes[i].err_msgs) {
1002 const err_code_struct *err = err_classes[i].err_msgs;
1003 for (j = 0; err[j].name; j++)
1004 if (num == err[j].code) {
1005 snprintf(ret, sizeof(ret), "%s - %s (%s)",
1006 err_classes[i].class, err[j].name, err[j].message);
1007 return ret;
1008 }
1009 }
1010
1011 snprintf(ret, sizeof(ret), "%s - %d", err_classes[i].class, num);
1012 return ret;
1013 }
1014
1015 snprintf(ret, sizeof(ret), "ERROR: Unknown error (%d,%d)", class, num);
1016 return(ret);
1017}

1880/*
1881 * return an NT error string from a SMB buffer
1882 */
1883const char *
1884nt_errstr(uint32_t err)
1885{
1886 static char ret[128];
1887 int i;
1888
1889 ret[0] = 0;
1890
1891 for (i = 0; nt_errors[i].name; i++) {
1892 if (err == nt_errors[i].code)
1893 return nt_errors[i].name;
1894 }
1895
1896 snprintf(ret, sizeof(ret), "0x%08x", err);
1897 return ret;
1898}
